column169: Aaron Rico Supervisor called safety to report a spill in trailer 551331, UN1090, ACETONE, 3, PG II. Aaron stated it looked to be a 1-gallon Pail leaked approximately 10oz of the product in the box it is packaged in and has saturated the box. Aaron stated the spill looks to be contained to the box it is packaged in and is still in the trailer but may h ave spilled on the trailer floor as well.~~~

During unloading operations at the Menomonee Falls 10-Day Facility, staff discovered a leak from a 5-gallon container of lithium preserved in mineral oil inside a trailer. The spill was limited to less than 2 gallons and remained confined within the trailer. Upon investigation, it was determined that the leak occurred due to improper securing of the load, which allowed the containers to shift during transportation. The spill was remediated by trained Veolia personnel and the container was properly closed.
column170: Veolia management will review with employees the importance of load securement, proper closure, and to use the proper containers for the waste.
